measure.CatchLine: Requires that lands zoned to allow density of one or fewer dwellings per acre to be considered a rural use.
measure.MeasureSummary:
Digest: This Act allow allows denser housing to be considered a rural use. (Flesch Readability Score: 60.7). 
	Requires that lands zoned to allow density of one or fewer dwellings per acre to be considered a rural use. Allows counties to rezone rural lands accordingly if the land is currently zoned for up to one dwelling per 2.5 acres.
measure.RelatingToFull: Relating to residential rural use of lands; creating new provisions; and amending ORS 197.734, 215.495 and 215.501.
measure.RelatingTo: Relating to residential rural use of lands.
measure.FiscalImpact: May have fiscal impact, but no statement yet issued
measure.RevenueImpact: May have revenue impact, but no statement yet issued

historyActions.ActionText: First reading. Referred to Speaker's desk.
